tal he is senior advisor on venture capital at sprie and advises on venture capital for china's zhongguancun science park martin haemmig earned his electronics degree in switzerland and his mba and doctorate in california and worked for almost 20 years in global high tech companies in asia europe and the us before returning to his academic career he became swiss national champion in marketing in 1994 downloads pdf+ seminar flyer modified may 2010 pdf martin_haemmig pdf 130.0 kb pdf+ green investing 2010 world economic forum report modified may 2010 pdf wef 2010_ _green_investing_re pdf 6.5 mb location philippines conference room encina hall 616 serra st 3rd floor stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact george krompacky parent research projects smart green cities project topics cleantech energy globalization venture capital water china europe india israel switzerland united states search sprie events of interest cross pacific venture investing comparing china and the us seminar series china's venture capital system and investment decision making wei zhang pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds stanford program on regions of innovation and entrepreneurship stanford graduate school of business knight management center mcclelland bldg 655 knight way stanford ca 94305 7298 tel 650 725 1885 fax 650 725 2198 mail code 7298
